$ /mnt/wslg/distro/

The same file system (for example → Linux/fhs/dev/sdX[`/dev/sdc`]) that is mounted to `/` is also mounted (read-only) to `/mnt/wslg/distro`.

code {
$ → Linux/shell/commands/sudo → Linux/shell/commands/mount | → Linux/shell/commands/grep '/mnt/wslg/distro'
→ Linux/fhs/dev/sdX[/dev/sdc] on /mnt/wslg/distro type ext4 (ro,relatime,discard,errors=remount-ro,data=ordered
code }

sa:

 `→ Linux/fhs/mnt/wslg`
